      • Notification

        public Notification(java.lang.String title,
                    java.lang.String message,
                    java.lang.String type,
                    java.lang.String userName,
                    java.lang.String borrowRecordId)
        This is the constructor that is used to instantiate the Notification object with all the necessary and provided parameters.
        Parameters:
        title - the title of the book about which the notification is being created.
        message - a message that is to be displayed in the notification.
        type - a type of the notification.
        userName - the username which needs to be notified.

      • Notification

        public Notification()
        This is the empty default constructor that is necessary for Firebase Database. We also use it when building up the class using the setters alone.
